15 Nov 2015 17:35






I liked this, simple as it was, until you got round to the punchline. A hypochondriac attention-seeking alarm bell found outside a primary school is a unified and rather amusing image, but the 'Boy Who Cried Wolf' parallels in the final log were far too blunt and on the nose for me and completely destroyed the credibility of the piece. It actually ends up reading like a -J, because the entire last log is so clearly contrived to make a clever reference. The basic concept of the last log was acceptable, but the 'anomalous canids' was what pushed it into joke territory for me.







